value: Can Scotland get out of their World Cup group? Just a win by THREE GOALS and we're there!
Only problem... we're playing the mighty Netherlands!
Will we regret our failure to beat the less mighty Peru and Iran?
Over to Mendoza we go...
PENALTY! NEVER!!
<h1>First blood to the Netherlands. We need FOUR now.<h1>
<h1>Fun fact! That was the 1000th goal in the history of the World Cup.<h1>
YESSS!!!
Bit more like it. Kenny Dalglish levels just before half time.
Dalglish went on to become Scotland's record cap-holder...
...and joint-record goalscorer.
PENALTY! ALSO NEVER (in all honesty)!!
And we're in front! Archie Gemmill does the business.
That penalty was gained by the often brilliant Graeme Souness...
...whose omission for the first two games is often cited as a reason for those bad results.
He didn't even get a sticker.
Oh, what's this?
GO ON WEE MAN!
Archie Gemmill has just scored the greatest goal in Scotland's history!
Even though I was only one at the time, I'm SURE I remember it.
JUST ONE TO GET!!
COME ON SCOTLAND!!!
That goal went on to take on a new place in Scottish culture...
<h1>....in an infamous scene in the Trainspotting movie.<h1>

But wait...

.

This looks ominous...

.
Oh dear. That was NOT in the script.
Thanks Johnny Rep. Two needed now.
But hardly any time....
And that's full time. A tragic tale.
So close and yet so very, very far...
This glorious failure...
...TYPIFIES what it is to be Scottish.
It is simply what we are destined...
...to endure.
